<TITLE> Indian army chief arrives in Dhaka </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, July 27 (bdnews24.com)  India's army chief General Deepak Kapoor arrived in Dhaka on Sunday on a six-day visit, the military's press wing said in a statement. His visit came five months after his Bangladesh counterpart General Moeen U Ahmed visited India in February with the promise of "ushering in a new era of close cooperation" between the two armies. Deepak is accompanied by his wife Kirti Kapoor and a four-member military delegation. Moeen's visit had seen the two armies agree to take new initiatives to deepen military cooperation, paving way for joint counter-terrorism exercises. The Indian army chief was received by Bangladesh Army's quarter master general Lt Gen Md Jahangir Alam Chowdhury at BAF Tarmac, Kurmitola, according to the Inter-Service Public Relations Directorate. Indian High Commissioner Pinak Ranjan Chakravarty was also present there. General Kapoor is expected to lay wreath at Shikha Anirban in Dhaka Cantonment and meet with president Iajuddin Ahmed and the chiefs of the army, air force and navy. He will also visit Dhaka Cantonment, National Museum, National Defence College, liberation war memorial sites in Comilla and other places of Bangladesh, the statement said. General Kapoor is scheduled to leave Dhaka on August 1, the statement added. bdnews
